ISO50 -- a 50% DIY computer keyboard

The hardware part is covered in directory ./hardware.

Firmware is based on TMK (https://github.com/tmk/tmk_keyboard); see
directory ./firmware. 'make program' should create the hex file
containing the firmware.

http://imgur.com/a/XgsYZ


The name of this project refers to the standard 105-key ISO keyboard
layout, reduced to 50 %.  It is not related to anything using the
photography-related connotation of the name.  It is not affiliated
with http://blog.iso50.com/.
